		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Water pollution</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Nrborderborderentrythreecolorsmay05-1-.JPG" class="image" title="Raw sewage and industrial waste flows into the U.S. from Mexico as the New River passes from Mexicali, Baja California to Calexico, California."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Nrborderborderentrythreecolorsmay05-1-.JPG/300px-Nrborderborderentrythreecolorsmay05-1-.JPG" width="300" height="225" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Nrborderborderentrythreecolorsmay05-1-.JPG" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
<a href="/wiki/Raw_sewage" title="Raw sewage" class="mw-redirect">Raw sewage</a> and <a href="/wiki/Industrial_waste" title="Industrial waste">industrial waste</a> flows into the U.S. from Mexico as the <a href="/wiki/New_River_(California)" title="New River (California)" class="mw-redirect">New River</a> passes from <a href="/wiki/Mexicali" title="Mexicali">Mexicali</a>, Baja California to <a href="/wiki/Calexico,_California" title="Calexico, California">Calexico, California</a>.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Water pollution</b> is the contamination of <a href="/wiki/Water" title="Water">water</a> bodies such as <a href="/wiki/Lake" title="Lake">lakes</a>, <a href="/wiki/River" title="River">rivers</a>, <a href="/wiki/Ocean" title="Ocean">oceans</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Groundwater" title="Groundwater">groundwater</a> caused by human activities, which can be harmful to organisms and plants that live in these water bodies.</p>
